          <msContents>
            <summary>A Persian prose translation of the Pahlavi original <title type="general">Ard&#x101; V&#x12B;r&#x101;f n&#x101;mak</title>, the story of Viraf, a
                            Parsee hermit, visiting the other world. <lb/> It has been a popular
                            work of which there is also a translation, into Persian, in verse and
                            more than one translation into English (see Rieu, BM 47b-48a). There are
                            also a number of critical modern translations, by Ghulam Reza
                            Rashld-Yasarm (Tehran H.S. 1314/ A.D. 1935), Muhammad Mu&#x2018;In (Tehran H.S,
                            1325/ A.D. 1946) and Rahim &#x2018;Afifi, including the Pahlavi text by Reza
                            Navabpour (Mashhad H.S. 1342/ A.D. 1963), see Mushar 153. T. </summary>
